## Chapter 2: TOGAF Framework Overview

### Learning Objectives ğŸ¯

By the end of this chapter, you will be able to:
- âœ… Explain what TOGAF is and why it's widely adopted
- âœ… Describe the key components of TOGAF
- âœ… Navigate the TOGAF Architecture Development Method (ADM)
- âœ… Understand TOGAF certification levels

---

### 2.1 What is TOGAF?

**Definition:**
> TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture Framework) is an enterprise architecture methodology and framework used to design, plan, implement, and govern enterprise information technology architecture.

**Key Facts:**
- **Publisher:** The Open Group
- **Current Version:** TOGAF 10 (released 2022)
- **License:** Open standard (free to use, must pay for certification)
- **Adoption:** Used by 80%+ of Forbes Global 50 companies
- **Industries:** All industries (IT, finance, healthcare, manufacturing, government, etc.)

**Why TOGAF?**
- âœ… **Industry Standard:** Common language across organizations
- âœ… **Comprehensive:** Covers all aspects of EA
- âœ… **Proven:** 30+ years of evolution and real-world use
- âœ… **Flexible:** Adaptable to any organization size or industry
- âœ… **Vendor-Neutral:** Not tied to specific technology vendors
- âœ… **Career Value:** TOGAF certification is globally recognized

---

### 2.2 TOGAF Framework Components

